Author: Zodiac<br />
Number: 21.10.2014<br />
Description:<br />
This programme is to synchronise a source file and a destination.<br />
Usage: <br />
After compile all java files to jar files, you can use following <br />
command to run this programme. <br />
* java -jar synserver.jar -file filename [-p serverport]
* java -jar synclient.jar -file filename -host hostname[-p serverport]
[-b blocksize] [-d direction] <br />

P.S: options of direction are "push" and "pull". "push" will push<br />
local files to remote server. "pull" will pull a local file from<br />
remote server to client


